comments.body:
Thank you for the patch [~wilfreds].
{code}
// If re-init is called before init the manager is null and the RM
// will crash, this happens in a number of tests.
{code}
I would say "Protect against uninitialized scheduling monitor manager"
In general I would try to update the test to call the init. The reason is that this check may hide important race conditions in the future and will lead the code crash later or miss monitoring due to an uninitialized monitor manager.
